{
  "doc_id": "8885",
  "text": "Two meta-analyses investigated the association between dairy products and gastric cancer risk [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . None of these analyses demonstrated a significant association between the intake of cheese and yoghurt, and gastric cancer risk. Of note, the results of cohort studies, but not case-control studies, suggested that total dairy intake might be related to the reduction of gastric cancer risk [CITATION_3] , whereas the results of case-control studies, but not cohort studies, provided weak evidence for an increased risk [CITATION_4] .",
